{"id":308265179,"question_id":2,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"4 years, 12 months","timestamp":1583059530,"status":14,"status_display":"Time Limit Exceeded","runtime":"N/A","url":"/submissions/detail/308265179/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"N/A","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * public class ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode next;\n *     ListNode(int x) { val = x; }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    public ListNode addTwoNumbers(ListNode l1, ListNode l2) {\n        ListNode a = l1;\n        ListNode b = l2;\n        int carry = 0;\n        int ans = 0;\n        int mul = 0;\n        while( a != null && b != null )\n        {\n            ans += (a.val + b.val) * Math.pow(10,mul++) ;\n            a = a.next; b = b.next;\n        }\n        while( b != null )\n        {\n            ans += b.val * Math.pow(10,mul++);\n        }\n        while( a != null )\n        {\n            ans += a.val * Math.pow(10,mul++);\n        }\n        ListNode l = new ListNode(ans%10);\n        ListNode t = l;\n        ans /= 10;\n        while ( ans != 0 )\n        {\n            ListNode temp = new ListNode(ans%10);\n            t.next = temp;\n            ans /= 10;\n            t = t.next;\n        }\n        return l;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
